  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I add more than one WordPress site in Godaddy's Deluxe hosting plan?",
  "response": "To add more than one WordPress site on GoDaddy's Deluxe hosting plan, you can follow these steps:\n\n### 1. Log in to Your GoDaddy Account\n- Go to the GoDaddy website and log in with your credentials.\n\n### 2. Access Your Hosting Account\n- From your account dashboard, navigate to the **\"My Products\"** section.\n- Under **\"Web Hosting,\"** find your Deluxe hosting plan and click on **\"Manage\"**.\n\n### 3. Install Additional WordPress Sites\nYou can use the GoDaddy Managed WordPress feature, or manually install WordPress for each site.\n\n#### a. Using the GoDaddy WordPress Installation Tool\n1. **In your hosting dashboard**, look for a section labeled **\"Install WordPress\"** or similar.\n2. Click on **\"Add site\"** or **\"Install WordPress\"**.\n3. Follow the prompts to set up the new WordPress site. You\u2019ll need to provide:\n   - Site name\n   - Admin email address\n   - Username and password\n4. Choose the domain name you want to associate with this WordPress installation. If you haven\u2019t created a new domain yet, you can also use subdomains.\n5. Click on **\"Install\"** and wait for the installation to complete.\n\n#### b. Manually Installing WordPress \nIf you prefer to install WordPress manually:\n1. **Download WordPress** from the [WordPress.org website](https://wordpress.org/download/).\n2. **Create a Database**:\n   - In your GoDaddy hosting panel, navigate to **\"Databases\"** and click on **\"MySQL\"**.\n   - Create a new database for your website and note your database name, username, and password.\n3. **Upload WordPress**:\n   - Use an FTP client like FileZilla or use the File Manager in GoDaddy's dashboard to upload the WordPress files to the desired directory (e.g., public_html/newfolder).\n4. **Set Up Configuration**:\n   - Go to your domain or subdomain to access the WordPress installation page (e.g., `yourdomain.com/newfolder`).\n   - Follow the on-screen instructions to complete the configuration using the database details you created earlier.\n5. **Finalize the Installation**:\n   - Fill in your site title, admin username, password, and email, then finish the installation.\n\n### 4. Manage Your Sites\nOnce you have multiple sites installed, you can manage them individually from the WordPress admin dashboard for each site.\n\n### 5. Visit Each Site\nYou can access your new sites by navigating to the respective domain or subdomain URLs in your browser.\n\n### Note\nEach site will be separate and can have its own plugins, themes, and content. Make sure to properly configure the DNS settings for your domains if needed.\n\nIf you encounter any issues or need more help, GoDaddy's customer support is available to assist you.",
